name: Green Depot
overview: Green Depot, Inc. supplies building products, services, and home solutions. It offers cleaning and recycling products, including hypo-allergenic cleaning, industrial cleaning, mold remediation, and recycling and composting products; lighting and electronics, which include CFL and LED light bulbs, incandescent light bulbs, power strips and energy monitors, chargers and flashlights, fans, lamps, and light fixtures; and paints and finishes, such as paints, brushes, rollers, accessories, caulks and sealants, wall finishes, coatings and sealants, strippers, and adhesives. The company also provides air and water filtration and safety products; baby products, including furniture, bedding, apparel, care, bottles, safety, and gifts; home dÐ¹cor products, such as rugs, tabletop, cabinets and countertops, window treatments, and outdoors; and baby, design, and reference books. In addition, Green Depot offers DIY toolboxes, flooring, carpet, insulation, framing, decking and molding, soundproofing, and ceilings and walls. The company also supplies products through its online store. Green Depot, Inc. was founded in 2005 and is based in Brooklyn, New York. It has stores in Manhattan, Brooklyn, and Greenport, New York; Chicago, Illinois; Stoneham, Massachusetts; Newark, New Jersey; and Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. The company also has distribution centers in Hartford, Connecticut; Newark, Delaware; Waldorf, Maryland; Manchester, New Hampshire; Pleasantville and Wall Township, New Jersey; and Albany, Farmingdale, Mattituck, and Newburgh, New York.
